---
import SeoLandingLayout from "../components/SeoLandingLayout.astro";

const page = {
  title: "AI Beauty Advisor — Get Personalized Makeup Recommendations",
  description:
    "Stop guessing. Our AI beauty advisor analyzes your face and recommends the exact makeup styles, products, and tutorials that work for your unique features.",
  faq: [
    {
      q: "Is this like talking to a real beauty advisor?",
      a: "Think of it as having a makeup artist who understands your face shape, skin undertone, and feature proportions — and can instantly show you what looks good before you commit to buying products or spending time on a tutorial.",
    },
    {
      q: "How accurate are the recommendations?",
      a: "The AI uses the same color analysis framework that professional stylists use (12-season color system) combined with facial feature analysis. Results are personalized to your actual face — not a generic 'what looks good on everyone' recommendation. However, we always note that AI suggestions are reference only, not professional beauty consultation.",
    },
    {
      q: "Can I use this if I'm a complete beginner?",
      a: "Yes. The AI recommends beginner-friendly styles first (minimal steps, forgiving techniques), and each recommendation comes with a step-by-step tutorial so you can actually recreate the look at home.",
    },
  ],
  relatedLinks: [
    { label: "AI Makeup Try-On", url: "/ai-makeup-try-on" },
    { label: "Makeup for Beginners", url: "/guides/beginner-tutorial" },
    { label: "Personal Color Analysis", url: "/diagnosis" },
    { label: "Pricing", url: "/pricing" },
  ],
};
---

<SeoLandingLayout {...page}>
  <Fragment slot="hero">
    <h1>
      Your AI Beauty Advisor: Makeup Recommendations That Actually Fit You
    </h1>
    <p>
      Not a generic quiz. An AI that analyzes your face, understands your
      features, and recommends the exact styles, products, and tutorials made
      for you.
    </p>
  </Fragment>

  <div class="seo-content">
    <h2>Why "What Looks Good on Me" Is the Hardest Makeup Question</h2>
    <p>
      Walk into any makeup store and you'll find thousands of products. Search
      on YouTube and you'll find thousands more tutorials. But none of them
      start with the one thing that actually matters: your face.
    </p>
    <p>
      Your AI beauty advisor flips that around. It starts with you — your skin
      tone, your face shape, your eye shape, your undertone — and works outward
      to recommend what actually looks good on <em>you</em>.
    </p>

    <h2>How the AI Advisor Works</h2>
    <div class="step-list">
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4>Upload a Selfie</h4>
          <p>
            One clear photo of your bare face in natural light. That's all the
            AI needs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4>Get a Diagnosis Report</h4>
          <p>
            The AI analyzes your skin undertone (warm/cool/neutral), face shape,
            eye shape, and feature proportions.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4>Pick a Scenario</h4>
          <p>
            Commute, date night, interview, photo — tell the AI what you need
            makeup for today.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step-card">
        <div class="step-num">4</div>
        <div>
          <h4>Receive 3 Personalized Recommendations</h4>
          <p>
            Three styles tailored to your face, with try-on images, tutorials,
            and product picks.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>What Makes the Advice Different</h2>
    <p>
      Most makeup recommendations follow a template: "soft glam is great for
      everyone" or "a nude lip always works." The problem is that soft glam on
      hooded eyes requires a completely different eyeshadow technique than soft
      glam on almond eyes. And a nude lip that looks perfect on warm undertones
      will wash out cool undertones.
    </p>
    <p>
      The AI advisor doesn't give templates. It adapts every recommendation to
      your actual features — the same way a professional stylist would adjust
      their advice for each client, but in seconds instead of an hour-long
      consultation.
    </p>

    <h2>The Advisor Doesn't Stop at Styles</h2>
    <p>After recommending styles, it also tells you:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Which products to buy</strong> — real SKUs at three budget tiers (drugstore,
        mid-range, premium), matched to your skin tone.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Which products to skip</strong> — honest advice on what you don't
        need, so you don't waste money.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>What mistakes to avoid</strong> — common errors for your specific
        features (e.g., "don't apply blush this low on your cheeks").
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>How to check your work</strong> — self-assessment tips so you know
        if you got it right.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p>
        <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> AI recommendations are personalized references,
        not professional beauty consultation. Results may vary based on individual
        features and technique. Always use your own judgment.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="seo-cta" slot="cta">
    <div class="seo-cta-inner">
      <h2>Get Your Personalized Recommendations</h2>
      <p>
        Upload your photo and see what styles the AI recommends for your face.
      </p>
      <a href="/diagnosis" class="cta-btn">Start Your AI Diagnosis — Free</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="seo-related" slot="related">
    <div class="related-inner">
      <h3>Explore More</h3>
      <ul class="related-list">
        {
          page.relatedLinks.map((link) => (
            <li>
              <a href={link.url}>{link.label}</a>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</SeoLandingLayout>
